
==================================================================
  HACKATHON SOAK TEST — 90-min sessions, agent_network_designer
==================================================================
  Host        : https://neurosanhackathon-api.eastus.cloudapp.azure.com
  Pods        : 12
  VUs         : 2500 concurrent active participants
  Duration    : 120 min (24 snapshots every 5 min)
  Ramp        : 3 min at 14 user/sec
  Think time  : 5-15 min between turns (realistic reading pace)

  SESSION MODEL:
  • Each VU = 1 participant with a FIXED user_id for the full session
  • NGINX sticky cookie pins that user to ONE pod for 90 min
  • chat_context passed and grows each turn:
      Turn 1 (fresh design) → ~5k-15k tokens
      Turn 3 (refine)       → ~20k-40k tokens (history included)
      Turn 6 (deep refine)  → ~50k-80k tokens
  • Azure Blob: read + write on EVERY turn (not just session start)

  BOTTLENECKS TRACKED:
  1. Token quota burn (compounds as sessions age) → ETA to 10M
  2. Per-turn token escalation (turn 1 vs 3 vs 6 cost)
  3. Pod memory growth (growing context in RAM per pinned session)
  4. NGINX hot-pod (sticky imbalance → one pod saturates first)
  5. Azure Blob IOPS (grows with session depth, not just count)
  6. p95 latency drift (slow as pod memory/queue fills)
==================================================================

  Pod spec: cpu — req / — lim  | mem 2000Mi req / 3000Mi lim
  LLM slots: 50/pod × 12 pods = 600 total concurrent AI calls

  Ramping to 2500 VUs at 14 user/sec (~3 min)...

